<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-12-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-12-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="214" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">Thompson</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-12-08"><hi rend="italic">December 8,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring your telegram 30th November, Treasury Department states
                            merchandise may now be shipped duty free through United States from port
                            to port in Mexico under section 3005, Revised Statutes, as amended by
                            act of May 21, 1900, and regulations similar to those proposed under
                            section 3005 for goods from port to port in United States through
                            Mexico.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>